<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════
     SLIDE 3 — MALWARE OVERVIEW
═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="slide" id="s3" data-accent="E8941A" data-notes="Malware = malicious software. Cover all 6 types briefly. The infection flow diagram shows how most malware enters via social engineering first.">
  <div class="eyebrow" style="--accent:var(--amber);">Threat Type 01 · Malware</div>
  <h2>What is Malware?</h2>
  <div class="two-col" style="flex:1;">
    <div class="col">
      <p style="margin-bottom:12px;">Malware (malicious software) is any program intentionally designed to cause damage, steal data, or gain unauthorized access to systems.</p>
      <div class="three-col" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:10px;">
        <div class="card dark"><h3 style="color:#F0C060;">Virus</h3><p style="font-size:12px;">Attaches to files; executes and replicates when opened.</p></div>
        <div class="card dark"><h3 style="color:#F0C060;">Worm</h3><p style="font-size:12px;">Self-propagates across networks — no user action needed.</p></div>
        <div class="card dark"><h3 style="color:#F0C060;">Trojan</h3><p style="font-size:12px;">Disguised as legitimate software; opens backdoors.</p></div>
        <div class="card dark"><h3 style="color:#F0C060;">Spyware</h3><p style="font-size:12px;">Silently records keystrokes, credentials, and activity.</p></div>
        <div class="card dark"><h3 style="color:#F0C060;">Rootkit</h3><p style="font-size:12px;">Embeds in the OS kernel; extremely difficult to detect.</p></div>
        <div class="card dark"><h3 style="color:#F0C060;">Adware</h3><p style="font-size:12px;">Delivers unwanted ads; often bundles spyware.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col" style="justify-content:center;">
      <h3 style="color:#F0C060; margin-bottom:12px;">How Malware Infects a System</h3>
      <div class="flow">
        <div class="flow-step"><span class="fnum" style="color:#F0C060;">01</span> Malicious email attachment or infected download</div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">↓</div>
        <div class="flow-step"><span class="fnum" style="color:#F0C060;">02</span> User opens / executes the file</div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">↓</div>
        <div class="flow-step"><span class="fnum" style="color:#F0C060;">03</span> Payload installs silently in the background</div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">↓</div>
        <div class="flow-step"><span class="fnum" style="color:#F0C060;">04</span> Data stolen, system damaged, or backdoor opened</div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════
     SLIDE 4 — MALWARE CASE STUDY
═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="slide" id="s4" data-accent="E8941A" data-notes="This is one of the most dramatic malware stories. Emphasize: emotional social engineering ('I love you') was far more powerful than technical exploits. Led to new cybercrime laws.">
  <div class="eyebrow" style="--accent:var(--amber);">Case Study · Malware</div>
  <h2>ILOVEYOU Worm — May 4, 2000</h2>
  <div class="two-col" style="flex:1;">
    <div class="col">
      <div style="margin-bottom:10px;">
        <span class="badge badge-amber">Worm Attack</span>
        <span class="badge badge-red">Philippines Origin</span>
        <span class="badge badge-gray">10 Days · Global</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card dark" style="margin-bottom:14px;">
        <h3 style="color:#F0C060;">The Attack</h3>
        <p style="font-size:13px;">Spread as an email with subject line <em>"ILOVEYOU"</em> and attachment <code>LOVE-LETTER-FOR-YOU.txt.vbs</code> — a Visual Basic script disguised as a text file.</p>
      </div>
      <ul class="list" style="--accent:var(--amber);">
        <li>Infected over <strong>50 million computers</strong> in just 10 days</li>
        <li>Overwrote all .jpg, .mp3, and document files</li>
        <li>Self-replicated by emailing <em>every Outlook contact</em></li>
        <li>Downloaded a password-stealing trojan from a remote server</li>
        <li>Caused an estimated <strong>$10 billion</strong> in damages</li>
        <li>Disabled systems at the Pentagon, CIA, and UK Parliament</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <div class="card accented" style="--accent:var(--amber); margin-bottom:14px;">
        <h3 style="color:#F0C060;">Why It Was So Effective</h3>
        <p>Social engineering — the emotional lure of "I love you" — bypassed technical defenses entirely. People <strong>wanted</strong> to open it.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card dark" style="margin-top:14px;">
        <h3 style="color:#F0C060;">Payload Chain</h3>
        <div class="flow" style="gap:4px;">
          <div class="flow-step" style="padding:7px 12px; font-size:12px;"><span class="fnum" style="color:#F0C060;">1</span>Open attachment → script executes</div>
          <div class="flow-arrow" style="font-size:12px;">↓</div>
