<div class="slide" id="s5" data-accent="2A6AE8" data-notes="Phishing is the #1 initial access vector. Emphasize the 4 types and the anatomy of a fake email. 3.4 billion phishing emails per day is a striking number.">
  <div class="eyebrow" style="--accent:var(--blue);">Threat Type 02 · Phishing</div>
  <h2>Phishing Attacks Explained</h2>
  <div class="two-col" style="flex:1;">
    <div class="col">
      <p style="margin-bottom:14px;">Phishing is a social engineering attack where attackers <strong>impersonate trusted entities</strong> to trick victims into revealing credentials, financial data, or installing malware.</p>
      <div class="three-col" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:10px;">
        <div class="card dark"><h3 style="color:#80AAFF;">Email Phishing</h3><p style="font-size:12px;">Mass emails mimicking banks, IT teams, or popular services.</p></div>
        <div class="card dark"><h3 style="color:#80AAFF;">Spear Phishing</h3><p style="font-size:12px;">Targeted — uses personal info to seem legitimate.</p></div>
        <div class="card dark"><h3 style="color:#80AAFF;">Whaling</h3><p style="font-size:12px;">Targets C-suite executives for high-value data access.</p></div>
        <div class="card dark"><h3 style="color:#80AAFF;">Smishing</h3><p style="font-size:12px;">Phishing via SMS — fake delivery or bank alerts.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="stats-row" style="margin-top:14px; margin-bottom:0;">
        <div class="stat"><span class="num" style="color:var(--blue);">3.4B</span><span class="lbl">Phishing emails sent daily</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><span class="num" style="color:var(--blue);">36%</span><span class="lbl">Of breaches involve phishing</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <h3 style="color:#80AAFF; margin-bottom:10px;">Anatomy of a Phishing Email</h3>
      <ul class="list" style="--accent:var(--blue);">
        <li>Spoofed sender (e.g. <code>support@paypa1.com</code>)</li>
        <li>Urgency: <em>"Your account will be suspended in 24h"</em></li>
        <li>Fake login page hosted on attacker's server</li>
        <li>Embedded malicious link masked with URL shorteners</li>
        <li>Grammatical errors or slightly off branding</li>
        <li>Requests for credentials, OTP codes, or payment</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

