<div class="slide" id="s9" data-accent="1AAE6A" data-notes="Defense in depth. Emphasize the 3-2-1 backup rule and that MFA stops the majority of credential-based attacks. Security awareness training is often the highest-ROI investment.">
  <div class="eyebrow" style="--accent:var(--green);">Defense &amp; Prevention</div>
  <h2>How to Defend Against Each Threat</h2>
  <div class="three-col" style="flex:1; align-content:start;">
    <div class="card">
      <h3 style="color:#F0C060;">vs. Malware</h3>
      <ul class="list" style="--accent:var(--amber);">
        <li>Deploy reputable antivirus / EDR solution</li>
        <li>Keep OS and all applications updated</li>
        <li>Never open unknown email attachments</li>
        <li>Use application whitelisting</li>
        <li>Segment network to limit spread</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3 style="color:#80AAFF;">vs. Phishing</h3>
      <ul class="list" style="--accent:var(--blue);">
        <li>Enable advanced email spam filtering</li>
        <li>Verify sender domains carefully</li>
        <li>Enable MFA on all accounts</li>
        <li>Regular security awareness training</li>
        <li>Deploy DMARC / SPF / DKIM protocols</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3 style="color:#F07070;">vs. Ransomware</h3>
      <ul class="list" style="--accent:var(--red);">
        <li>Follow the <strong>3-2-1 backup rule</strong></li>
        <li>Patch systems immediately upon release</li>
        <li>Restrict admin privileges (least privilege)</li>
        <li>Monitor for unusual file encryption</li>
        <li>Maintain an incident response plan</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

